    <note>Wang(2) Bin(2) [1859] His father and grandfather followed their kinsman (zuren), Wang(2) Chao [3937] to Min at the end of the Tang. They both then sailed to Xinlo (Silla) where they were employed by the government. When Bin(2) was 18, he used the 'foreign student quota' (bingong) to enter the imperial university. Zongwang's [1904] grandfather. XCB, 109.5b; SS, 304.22a-22b; Sanshan zhi, 26.7a. CBD, 1, 169-70.</note>
